#rd(u) #rd(u)

(2)

where the received trust (#rt) and the received distrust (#rd) represent the number of trust and distrust edges to the node u, respectively.
Controversy was studied by [8] and [17] in the context of recommender systems, where controversial reviews are deï¬ned as those reviews that receive a variety of high and low scores, reï¬‚ecting disagreement about reviews. Those studies introduced a measure of controversy in terms of standard deviation Ïƒ of the reviews of an item i and the level of disagreement Î± deï¬ned as follows:

